The paper deals with optimizing the pricing of human computation tasks, which falls under the category of human computation (cs.HC). The paper also leverages decision theory and Markov Decision Processes, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational economics (cs.CE). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which can fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT).
